# Git & Commit Conventions

## Commit messages — English only

Format: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>`

| Type | Use for |
|------|---------|
| `feat` | New feature |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `refactor` | Code change, no behavior change |
| `test` | Tests only |
| `docs` | Documentation |
| `chore` | Tooling, deps |
| `perf` | Performance |
| `ci` | CI/CD |

Examples:

```
feat(web): add pad sidebar layout
fix(api): handle 401 in auth client
test(h5): add login form smoke test
```

- Subject: imperative mood, ≤50 chars, no period at end
- Scope: `h5`, `web`, `ui`, `api`, `shared-types`, or omit

## Commit message body

- Optional bullet points after a blank line (why / what changed)
- **No Git trailers** in commit messages unless the user explicitly asks for human co-author attribution
- **Never** append `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` — Cursor IDE may inject this; strip it before committing
- Do not add `Signed-off-by`, `Co-authored-by`, or similar footer lines by default

## Before commit

```bash
pnpm lint && pnpm typecheck && pnpm test && pnpm audit
```

Fix critical/high audit findings before merging.

## Do not

- Chinese commit messages
- Vague messages: `fix bug`, `update`, `wip`
- Commit `.env`, secrets, or `dist/` artifacts
- `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` or any unsolicited attribution trailers

## Git hooks

Repo hooks live in `.githooks/`. After clone, run `pnpm install` (sets `core.hooksPath`) or:

```bash
git config core.hooksPath .githooks
```

`prepare-commit-msg` removes Cursor co-author lines automatically.
